sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Producer Client
    participant Redis as Redis<br/>6379/TCP
    participant AP as Async Processor<br/>(llm-d-async)
    participant Gate as Flow Control Gate
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>9090/TCP
    participant IGW as Inference Gateway<br/>80/443 TCP
    participant vLLM as vLLM Model Server

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 1: Async Inference Request (Redis Sorted Set)

    Client->>Redis: ZADD request-sortedset<br/>(score=deadline, JSON payload)<br/>Optional TLS, Password auth

    loop Poll interval (configurable, default 1000ms)
        AP->>Redis: ZPOPMIN request-sortedset<br/>(batch size, earliest deadline first)<br/>Optional TLS, Password auth
    end

    AP->>Gate: Budget() - check dispatch allowance

    alt Prometheus-based gate
        Gate->>Prom: PromQL query<br/>(pool saturation / queue size)<br/>HTTP 9090/TCP
        Prom-->>Gate: Metric value
        Gate-->>AP: Budget (0.0 - 1.0)
    else Redis-based gate
        Gate->>Redis: GET budget key<br/>6379/TCP
        Redis-->>Gate: Budget value
        Gate-->>AP: Budget (0.0 - 1.0)
    end

    Note over AP: batch = floor(configured_batch x budget)

    AP->>IGW: HTTP POST /inference<br/>JSON payload + x-gateway-inference-objective header<br/>Configurable TLS 1.2+ / optional mTLS
    IGW->>vLLM: Forward inference request
    vLLM-->>IGW: Inference result
    IGW-->>AP: HTTP 200 JSON response

    AP->>Redis: LPUSH result-list<br/>(JSON result)<br/>Optional TLS, Password auth

    Client->>Redis: BRPOP result-{requestID}<br/>(blocking wait for result)<br/>Optional TLS, Password auth
    Redis-->>Client: JSON result

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 2: Retry with Exponential Backoff

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
        AP->>AP: Worker receives retryable error<br/>(429 rate-limit or 5xx server error)
        AP->>Redis: ZADD retry-sortedset<br/>(score = now + backoff)<br/>Backoff: 2s base, 60s cap, equal jitter

        loop Adaptive poll (1s-30s backoff when idle)
            AP->>Redis: ZRANGEBYSCORE retry-sortedset<br/>(score <= now) + ZREM (atomic Lua script)
        end

        AP->>AP: Re-dispatch to request channel
        Note over AP: Retries until request deadline expires
    end

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 3: Graceful Shutdown (SIGTERM)

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over AP: SIGTERM received
        AP->>Redis: Re-enqueue in-flight requests<br/>(ZADD back to request sorted set)
        AP->>Redis: Flush buffered results<br/>(LPUSH remaining results)
        Note over AP: Drain context ensures retry + result workers complete
    end
